query.result:
43 Then, as cranes which to the Rife mountains 44 would fly part, and part towards the sands, 45 these fleeing the cold, those the sun,
46 one people go, the other come; 47 and return, weeping, to the first songs 48 and to the shouting which more suits them;
49 and draw near to me, as before, 50 those same who had begged me, 51 attentive to listen in their faces.

58 From here upwards I go so as not to be more blind;
59 a woman is above who gains me grace,
